# Firas AI — environment variables (ALL OPTIONAL)
#
# The local server (server.mjs) uses OLLAMA by default at http://localhost:11434
# and falls back to the FREE keyless https://text.pollinations.ai engine if
# Ollama is unreachable. No keys are required for normal use — the *-cloud
# Ollama models run via your signed-in Ollama account, NOT an API key here.
#
# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in only what you need. NEVER commit ".env"
# or the data/ directory (it holds the database + the session secret).

# --- Sessions / accounts ----------------------------------------------------
# Secret used to sign session cookies (HMAC-SHA256). If unset, the server
# generates one once and persists it in the DB (db.secret). Set this explicitly
# in production so sessions survive a db reset and stay private.
# SESSION_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-hex-string

# --- Persistent database via Firebase (FREE, no card — recommended for deploy)
# By default the DB is a local JSON file (data/db.json), which is WIPED on hosts
# with no persistent disk (Render free, etc.) → accounts + chat history reset.
# Set BOTH of these to store the DB in your Firebase Realtime Database instead,
# so everything persists for free. The server authenticates as a SERVICE ACCOUNT
# (admin), so the database can stay in LOCKED mode (no public rules needed).
#   1. Firebase Console -> Build -> Realtime Database -> Create Database -> copy
#      its URL into FIREBASE_DB_URL.
#   2. Project Settings -> Service accounts -> Generate new private key -> paste
#      the WHOLE downloaded JSON (one line) into FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT.
# FIREBASE_DB_URL=https://your-project-default-rtdb.firebaseio.com
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT={"type":"service_account","project_id":"...","private_key":"-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n","client_email":"...@....iam.gserviceaccount.com"}

# --- Google / Firebase sign-in (optional social login) ----------------------
# Enables POST /api/auth/firebase, which verifies a Google/Firebase ID token
# (RS256 JWT, validated server-side against Google's public x509 certs — zero
# npm deps) and logs the user in with the same signed session cookie as email
# login. Set this to your Firebase project ID (the token's "aud" claim, and the
# issuer https://securetoken.google.com/<project-id>). If UNSET, the endpoint
# returns 501 "social sign-in not configured" and social login is disabled.
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-firebase-project-id

# --- Ollama engine (default) ------------------------------------------------
# Base URL for the Ollama native API. Default: http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
#
# DEPLOYING ONLINE (no local Ollama on the host)? Point at Ollama's hosted cloud
# API and add a key — then text + vision work from any server (Vercel, a VPS...):
#   OLLAMA_HOST=https://ollama.com
#   OLLAMA_API_KEY=your-ollama-cloud-key
# Get a key at https://ollama.com (account -> keys). On the cloud API, model tags
# may differ (e.g. no "-cloud" suffix) and you must pick a cloud VISION model —
# set OLLAMA_MODEL_* and OLLAMA_MODEL_VISION accordingly.
#
# Tier -> model overrides (defaults verified working 2026-06-26). NOTE: Ollama
# cloud retires models over time — if a tier returns empty, run `ollama list`
# and swap to a current cloud model here.
# OLLAMA_MODEL_MINI=gpt-oss:120b-cloud
# OLLAMA_MODEL_PRO=gpt-oss:120b-cloud
# OLLAMA_MODEL_ULTRA=qwen3-coder:480b-cloud
# OLLAMA_MODEL_MAX=qwen3-coder:480b-cloud   # last-resort engine for the Max tier
#
# Vision/multimodal model — used AUTOMATICALLY when a request carries images
# (any message with a non-empty "images" array). Independent of tier; think is
# forced OFF for vision. Default: qwen2.5vl:7b (verified installed locally).
# OLLAMA_MODEL_VISION=qwen2.5vl:7b

# --- Firas MAX tier engines (the 👑 "Max" tier) -----------------------------
# Max runs a fallback CHAIN so the strongest available engine answers, capped per
# user per day (MAX_DAILY_LIMIT, default 10):
#     Claude Sonnet (paid)  ->  OpenRouter free (DeepSeek-R1)  ->  Ollama / pollinations
# Set NEITHER and Max just uses your free Ollama model (OLLAMA_MODEL_MAX).
#
# 1) OpenRouter — FREE, no credit card. Gives Max a frontier free model. Get a key
#    at https://openrouter.ai/keys (sign up -> Keys -> Create). Default model is the
#    strongest current FREE option (NVIDIA Nemotron Ultra 550B). DeepSeek-R1 is now
#    PAID on OpenRouter — set OPENROUTER_MODEL=deepseek/deepseek-r1 (+ add credit) for it.
#    See the live free list at https://openrouter.ai/models?max_price=0
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=nvidia/nemotron-3-ultra-550b-a55b:free
#
# 2) Claude (Anthropic) — PAID (per-token, needs account credit). If set AND it has
#    balance, Max uses it FIRST (highest quality); when credit runs out it auto-
#    falls back to OpenRouter above. Leave unset if your balance is 0.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# ANTHROPIC_MAX_TOKENS=8192
#
# Per-user daily cap for the Max tier (default 10).
# MAX_DAILY_LIMIT=10

# --- Image generation: Gemini-quality for FREE (optional) -------------------
# Images work KEYLESS by default (pollinations flux + enhance). The chain, in order:
#   Puter (best, free)  ->  Gemini  ->  Hugging Face  ->  keyless pollinations
#
# Puter.com — real GPT-Image / Gemini "Nano Banana" quality, called SERVER-SIDE with
# YOUR developer auth token so END USERS never sign in to Puter. We tried it first.
#   1. Sign in at https://puter.com  ->  https://puter.com/dashboard#account
#   2. In "API token", click Create token (copied to clipboard); paste below.
# ⚠ REALITY CHECK (tested 2026-06-28): Puter's "User-Pays" free credit is a SMALL one-
# time balance on YOUR account — a few images, then HTTP 402 "insufficient_funds". The
# expensive models (gpt-image-2 "high", gemini "nano-banana") drain it instantly; the
# CHEAP ones (gpt-image-1-mini, gpt-image-2 "low") last a bit longer. For sustained use
# you must ADD CREDITS to your Puter account (paid) — gpt-image-1-mini is the cheapest,
# ~cents/image, and still excellent. When the balance is 0 the chain auto-falls back to
# Hugging Face / keyless pollinations (free), and Puter is skipped for 10 min.
# To truly avoid ALL per-image cost AND keep Gemini/GPT quality, you must instead let
# each user sign in to Puter client-side (each brings their own free credits) — but that
# requires a per-user Puter login, which this server-side setup intentionally avoids.
# PUTER_AUTH_TOKEN=eyJ...your-puter-token
# PUTER_IMAGE_MODEL=gpt-image-2        # DEFAULT. Sharper + better in-image text. Use gpt-image-1-mini for cheapest / most images per credit. Also: gpt-image-1.5, nano-banana (=gemini-2.5-flash-image), nano-banana-pro
# PUTER_IMAGE_QUALITY=low              # DEFAULT. gpt-image-2 / gpt-image-1.5 only: low | medium | high (mini ignores it). "high"/"medium" + nano-banana cost more & 402 sooner.
#
# To reach actual Gemini ("Nano Banana") quality + in-image text + editing, add a FREE
# Google AI Studio key (no credit card, ~500 images/day): https://aistudio.google.com
# -> Get API key. When set, /api/image uses Gemini after Puter and falls back to keyless
# pollinations automatically on error/quota.
# GEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...your-free-key   (note: Gemini IMAGE gen needs Google billing)
# GEMINI_IMAGE_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-image
#
# Or Cloudflare Workers AI — the most RELIABLE truly-FREE option (no per-image cost,
# no card, no user login). 10,000 neurons/day free ≈ ~150-200 images/day. Quality is
# FLUX.1-schnell (≈ pollinations, NOT gpt-image/Gemini), so use it as a dependable free
# fallback after Puter, before keyless pollinations. Setup:
#   1. Create a free account at https://dash.cloudflare.com
#   2. Account ID: on the dashboard URL (dash.cloudflare.com/<ACCOUNT_ID>) or any zone's
#      Overview → "Account ID".
#   3. API token: My Profile → API Tokens → Create Token → use the "Workers AI" template
#      (or a custom token with the Account › Workers AI › Read+Edit permission).
# CF_ACCOUNT_ID=your-cloudflare-account-id
# CF_API_TOKEN=your-workers-ai-api-token
# CF_IMAGE_MODEL=@cf/black-forest-labs/flux-1-schnell
# CF_IMAGE_STEPS=6        # flux-schnell: 1-8 (higher = better/slower)
#
# Or Hugging Face FLUX.1-schnell (FREE token, no card) — lossless PNG output.
# Get a token at https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens (read scope). Tried after
# Gemini, before keyless pollinations. Free tier has limited monthly credits/rate.
# NOTE: only FLUX.1-schnell is still served FREE by hf-inference — FLUX.1-dev, SDXL
# and SD3.5 now return 410/400 (need a PAID provider). schnell is the fast 4-step
# model: clean PNGs, but NOT clearly better than keyless pollinations' flux+enhance
# (which is richer but lossy JPEG). For true Gemini quality, add Google billing above.
# HF_API_KEY=hf_...your-free-token
# HF_IMAGE_MODEL=black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-schnell

# --- Free keyless default (no key required) ---------------------------------
# POLLINATIONS_MODEL=openai

# --- Security (recommended when deploying publicly over HTTPS) --------------
# Mark session cookies Secure (HTTPS-only). Leave unset for local http://.
# SECURE_COOKIES=1
# Trust the X-Forwarded-For header for rate-limiting ONLY when behind a trusted
# reverse proxy (nginx/Vercel). Off by default so clients can't spoof their IP.
# TRUST_PROXY=1

# --- Misc -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Restrict CORS to a specific origin (api/chat.js). Default: empty = same-origin only.
# ALLOWED_ORIGIN=https://your-site.example
# Upstream abort timeout in milliseconds (default 120000).
# REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS=120000
